{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|よる}}

{{IPAfont|⟨yo<sub>1</sub>ru⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/jʷoru/}} → {{IPAchar|/joru/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=よる|-}}.

Derived from ''yo'' below, suffixed with an element ''ru'' of unclear meaning.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>  Compare {{m|ja|日||tr=hi|[[day]]}} → {{m|ja|昼||tr=hiru|[[daytime]]}}, which seems to use this same ''ru'' element.<ref name="KDJ"/>

Now the most common term for {{m|en|night}} in modern {{cog|ja|-}}.

{{ja-noun|よる}}

# [[night]], [[evening]]
#: {{ja-usex|sort=よる|[[東京]]の'''夜'''|^とうきょう の '''よる'''|Tokyo '''nights'''}}
#: {{ja-usex|[[不安]]な'''夜'''を[[過ごす]]|ふあん な '''よる''' を すごす|to endure a '''night''' of anxiety|lit=to pass an '''uneasy''' night}}
#: {{ja-usex|'''夜'''の[[星空]]を[[見上げる]]|'''よる''' の ほしぞら を みあげる|to look up at the '''night'''<nowiki/>'s starry sky}}
#: {{ja-usex|『[[w:ja:夜のヒットスタジオ|'''夜'''のヒットスタジオ]]』|『^'''よる''' の ^ヒット ^スタジオ』|"Hit Studio of the '''Night'''" {{gloss|prominent Japanese music show}}}}
#: {{syn|ja|夜間|tr=yakan}}
#: {{ant|ja|昼|tr=hiru}}

